Information
------------------------------

Penelope Keith's Hidden Villages
Dame Penelope Keith knows a thing or two about village life, having lived in one for almost four decades. But as well as having inside knowledge, she's also the most charming of companions for these gentle travelogues that peek beneath the surface of our quintessentially British, picturesque villages.




2)  Cumbria 
Penelope learns about life in Cumbria, beginning in Coniston, a village that has tackled everything from copper mining to hill farming and high-class Victorian tourism to the speed records of Donald Campbell. Further north, Penelope meets the community buying its local mountain, before indulging in the unique Cumbrian pursuit of hound trailing.
